passing f to d3.mean function call in the variance implementation

Fix hierarchy.revalue.

Post-order traversal alone causes all parent values to be reset to zero
*after* accumulating child values.

An additional pre-order traversal resets all parent values to zero
first, and the post-order traversal can then accumulate child values in
their parents.

This only affects sticky treemaps.

Merge pull request #1873 from mserinjane/master

removing .js extension from the 'main' property

Don’t store temporary variables on tree nodes.

Rather than creating a temporary _tree hash on the tree nodes to store temporary
variables needed to compute the tree layout, the tree is wrapped. This
eliminates the risk of a namespace collision, and eliminates the need to
subsequently delete temporary variables. (They will be garbage collected.)

d3.shuffle a subset of an array and tests for d3.shuffle.

d3.shuffle takes two extra optional arguments that work on array
subsets: d3.shuffle(array[, i0[, i1]]). If given just array, then
shuffles entire array. If given array and i0, shuffles from index i0 to
the end of the array. If given array, i0, and i1, shuffles between i0
and i1. Tests for d3.shuffle also added.

See #1865.
